post_cb({"24832296": {"ParentId": "24831852", "PostTypeId": "2", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<p>In the standard C language, macros cannot generate preprocessing directives. For instance in the ISO 9899:1999 standard:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_24831852_24832296_0\">6.10.3.4 Rescanning and further replacement</p>\n<p id=\"so_24831852_24832296_1\">[ ... ]</p>\n<p id=\"so_24831852_24832296_2\">The resulting completely macro-replaced preprocessing token sequence is not processed\n  as a preprocessing directive even if it resembles one, [ ... ]</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>(This \"even if it resembles one\" remark is completely superfluous because, of course, no syntax is ever treated as a preprocessing directive if it does <strong>not</strong> resemble one! Yet, the words stick in your mind for years. I just located the quote's section by searching the document for the string \"resembles one\".)</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1250772", "LastEditorUserId": "1250772", "LastEditDate": "2014-07-18T19:27:02.547", "Id": "24832296", "Score": "4", "CreationDate": "2014-07-18T19:21:41.763", "LastActivityDate": "2014-07-18T19:27:02.547"}, "24831852": {"CommentCount": "1", "ViewCount": "134", "CreationDate": "2014-07-18T18:49:36.947", "LastActivityDate": "2014-07-18T19:27:02.547", "Title": "Can I define a macro that defines macros ?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "24832296", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "24831852", "Score": "6", "Body": "<p>The question came to mind by looking at the memory leak detection mechanism in VS. There the following boilerplate code is needed : </p>\n<pre><code>#define _CRTDBG_MAP_ALLOC\n#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;\n#include &lt;crtdbg.h&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>but replacing this code with <code>DETECT_MLEAKS</code> : </p>\n<pre><code>#define DETECT_MLEAKS\\\n#define _CRTDBG_MAP_ALLOC\\\n#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;\\\n#include &lt;crtdbg.h&gt;\\\n</code></pre>\n<p>can't be done. </p>\n<p>Are there any workarounds - suggestions ? </p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><macros>", "OwnerUserId": "2567683", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_24831852_24832296_2": {"section_id": 532, "quality": 0.9230769230769231, "length": 12}}, "n3337": {"so_24831852_24832296_2": {"section_id": 523, "quality": 0.9230769230769231, "length": 12}}, "n4659": {"so_24831852_24832296_2": {"section_id": 553, "quality": 0.9230769230769231, "length": 12}}}, "24832007": {"ParentId": "24831852", "CommentCount": "0", "Body": "<pre><code>//#define DETECT_MLEAKS //Uncomment to detect mem-leaks\n#ifdef DETECT_MLEAKS\n#define _CRTDBG_MAP_ALLOC\n#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;\n#include &lt;crtdbg.h&gt;\n#endif\n</code></pre>\n<p>Is how I typically do such things.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "1756405", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "24832007", "Score": "6", "CreationDate": "2014-07-18T18:59:55.393", "LastActivityDate": "2014-07-18T18:59:55.393"}});